[It remains interesting that only a single jar of the curry sauce has
been implicated in being a vehicle for botulism. This observation
might lead one to consider that the storage of the container was
suboptimal and this may have led to enough growth of the botulinum
bacillus to lead to toxin production. - Mod.LL]
